The Special Adviser to Governor Adegboyega Oyetola, Oluomo Sunday Akere has commended the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) on the introduction of BVAS electronic machines in casting votes. Akere said the introduction of the machine is a serious improvement in the voting processes.Â He stressed further that the machine has made the election peaceful. He explained that by 2023, INEC should be able to offer fully automated electronic system for the election. Akere, who voted at his unit 3, ward 6, Oja Iloro Igbajo in Boluwaduro local council area of the state, noted that the exercise was less stressful as people came to cast their votes and returned home. On the outcome of the election, Akere expressed assurance that his principal, Adegboyega Oyetola will emerge victorious.